France ' s high - speed trains go double - decker . France on Thursday introduced double - decker trains in its high - speed TGV service to cope with growing traffic on its busiest Paris - Lyon route . The state railway company SNCF said the blue - and - grey trains carried 516 passengers , 40 percent more than a conventional TGV train , at the same speed of 270 kph ( 170 mph ) . 
